The paper discusses the need for architectural innovations in wireless networks to support programmability, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also covers topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cognitive radio (cs.CR), which are relevant to wireless communication. The paper also discusses software-defined networking (SDN) and virtualization, which are related to control systems (cs.SY) and architecture (cs.AR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI, followed by cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.AR.
